article.headline: UNLV 103, Norfolk State 56
article.story: LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Jo'Van Adams' 20 points led UNLV to a 103-56 victory over Norfolk State on Monday, the Rebels fifth-straight win. Kevin Kruger added 18 points and seven assists for the Rebels, who improved to 9-2. UNLV opened the game on a 23-4 run, fueled by three 3-pointers by Kruger and 2-for-9 shooting. Spartans contributed three turnovers, and by halftime, UNLV led 55-28 on 70.4 percent shooting from the field. Kruger finished 6-for-8 from the field, and Adams made all four of his 3-point tries. Norfolk State (1-7) was led by Raphael Hall, who had 12 points. Tynell Dunkley and Calvin Brown each added 11 points. Dunkley also had a game-high 11 rebounds. The margin of victory was the widest for the Rebels since 1998, when UNLV beat Sacred Heart by the same score.
